Class oracle.html.MetaInfo 

java.lang.Object
   |
   +----oracle.html.MetaInfo
public class MetaInfo
extends Object
implements IHtmlItem
Description:

MetaInfo class encapsulates META element as specified in HTML2

Instructions:

It's simple to create a MetaInfo Object. Simply invoke its constructor and supply the necessary parameters.
Then you can add the object to the HtmlHead object.

Example: 

// Create a MetaInfo Object
MetaInfo meta = new MetaInfo("Expires", "28 Feb, 1996");
// Add MetaInfo object to HtmlHead head (assuming it's been created)
head.addMetaInfo(meta);
